# Copy to .env and fill in. .env is gitignored — never commit real keys.
#
# You do NOT need any of these to develop or test. `cargo test`, `cargo xtask ci`,
# and `exub scan` run against the built-in MOCK adapters — keyless and offline. Fill
# a key in only when you wire and select that real provider.
#
# Secrets use provider-NATIVE names (MASSIVE_API_KEY, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, …) and come
# from the environment only — never the config file. Non-secret config uses EXUB_*.
# See .rules for the guardrails.

# --- Market-data feeds (Phase 7+) ---
# Massive (formerly Polygon.io) — read by market-data's MassiveSource (stub until Phase 7).
MASSIVE_API_KEY=
# Alpha Vantage — historical options w/ IV; free tier is heavily rate-limited (~25 req/day).
# ALPHA_VANTAGE_API_KEY=

# --- AI model keys — NOT NEEDED, by design ---
# The engine contains no LLM code. Agents (Claude Code, Gemini CLI, Codex) connect over MCP
# and bring their own model + key; exuberance never reads ANTHROPIC/OPENAI/GEMINI keys.
# (ROADMAP Phases 15–16 tombstone.)

# --- Broker credentials — NOT NEEDED, by design ---
# The engine places no orders; execution was cut (ROADMAP Phases 19–22 tombstone). No broker
# credential is ever read. You trade in your own brokerage.

# --- Non-secret config (EXUB_*; also settable via flags / a --config TOML) ---
# Vestigial: the engine has no execution path regardless; kept for the dormant broker seam.
EXUB_TRADING_MODE=paper
# Persistent IV-history store (Phase 8). Unset → an ephemeral in-memory store; set a path to
# accumulate daily IV across runs so `iv_rank` becomes computable. Also `--store PATH`.
# EXUB_STORE_PATH=~/.local/share/exuberance/iv.db
